lt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":null,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":null,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"0\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"0\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"0\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"0\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"0\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"0\",\"show_email_icon\":\"0\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"0\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}', '16', '0', '10', '', '', '1', '2', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '0', '*', ''), ('28', '88', 'Competitive Levels based on ITN', 'competitive-levels-based-on-itn', '', '<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">The Competitive Levels based on International Tennis Number (ITN) and defined by the International Tennis Federation (ITF) are:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">Elite</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-1: The player is currently capable of maintaining the ATP / WTA classification. A player of international class, devoted to international competition and whose main sources of input are the tournaments with cash prizes. This player has a wide experience in the professional circuit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">Advanced</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-2: The player has the ability to analyze and explore the weaknesses of the opponent. It can change its strategy and style of play and run shots consisting of difficult situations. Normally it is a player with a high rating at the national level.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-3: The player has good anticipation and frequently has consistent shots around which to base his game. The player has \"competitive ability\", plays tennis treating the percentage of shots and regularly has the ability to return winner hits or force the opponent’s mistakes with backspin shots closed to the net.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-4: The player plays consistently. It is capable of emitting power and effects with efficiency, and began to control the speed of the ball. It has a good foretaste, and effectively defends the weak points. Can control depth of shots and begins to vary game plan according to opponents. Although difficult shots with occasional uncertainties, is capable of performing the first service with power and precision. It is capable, in any case, to position the second service. In doubles, normally plays aggressively.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\"> Intermediate</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-5: Good consistency (solid shots), has control of direction and depth, both in straight and the reverse, with moderate strokes, although it may lose the knock up due to impatience. Ability to play lobs, closing with power points, net-shots and smashes with good success rate. It covers the court well, with experience and tactical knowledge, but does not yet have a good tennis-oriented percentage of shots.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-6: It has improved the consistency of strokes with directional control on moderate ones, but with little depth and variety. Is improving in covering the court, but is still hesitant to get to the net. He is learning to play doubles.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-7: Pretty solid play in the shots with moderate speed, but still denotes certain timidity about the shots of the most difficult and can make mistakes when seeking direction, depth or power. Individually plays the game most of the end zone even if in doubles the positions are usually one close to the net and one to the back.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">Beginner – Intermediate</span></span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-8: He is learning to control the direction of the ball, although much still needs to improve the coverage of the court. Playing with other players of his level can sustain a short rally, with low rhythm, with some consistency. Playing in doubles normally remains in the initial position.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-9: Need being experience on the court. Although it may make the shots with some success, their weakness is evident. It is familiarizing with the basic positions to play individual or doubles matches, it still needs to improve in this aspect, and may prefer to play including these two variations of the game from the back of the court. This player has begun to play games. He is learning the basic rules and scoring system.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-10: This player is starting to play competitions (he can serve, respond and knock up) using normal balls, approved by the ITF.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">Beginner</span></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-10.1: The player is able to knock up with movement and control.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-10.2: The player has some basic and specific skills to hit the tennis ball that regularly receives, but still with no movement and dribbling control.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial;\">ITN-10.3: The player has just started playing tennis and is at the early stages of developing their tennis skills and is primarily learning tasks and coordination exercises.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '1', '0', '0', '25', '2012-03-01 19:48:44', '42', 'Administrator', '2012-05-17 20:49:55', '42', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-03-01 19:48:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":null,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\"